WEBVTT

00:05.436 --> 00:07.308
HOLD ON.
WHAT? WHAT´S WRONG?

00:07.308 --> 00:10.311
ANGIE´S DAD´S THERE. HE´S GONNA
WANT TO PLAY DOMINOES AGAIN.

00:10.311 --> 00:15.046
ALL WEEK IT´S BEEN, "GEORGE,
DOMINOES IS A MAN´S GAME.

00:15.046 --> 00:20.051
COME, SHOW ME WHAT KIND
OF MAN YOU ARE, CHICO!"

00:20.051 --> 00:22.323
AND, GEORGE, I BET
HE WOULDN´T BUG YOU

00:22.323 --> 00:25.156
IF HE FOUND SOMEONE ELSE
TO PLAY WITH.

00:27.728 --> 00:30.401
YOU KNOW, ERNIE, I´VE BEEN
HAVING TROUBLE WITH THIS LOCK.

00:30.401 --> 00:32.233
REALLY?

00:32.233 --> 00:33.434
YEAH. PULL IT.

00:33.434 --> 00:35.206
HERE WE GO. HA HA HA!

00:35.206 --> 00:37.738
ERNESTO!

00:37.738 --> 00:41.212
OH. HELLO.

00:41.212 --> 00:42.513
JOIN ME.

00:42.513 --> 00:44.775
DOMINOES IS A MAN´S GAME.

00:44.775 --> 00:46.317
COME...

00:46.317 --> 00:50.351
SHOW ME WHAT KIND OF MAN
YOU ARE, CHICO!

00:50.351 --> 00:52.653
HEY, YOU GOT
A PARTNER, VIC.

00:52.653 --> 00:55.356
I´LL CATCH YOUR GAME
TOMORROW NIGHT.

00:55.356 --> 00:58.289
OH, BUT YOU´RE LEAVING
TOMORROW.

00:58.289 --> 00:59.660
OH, I KNOW,

00:59.660 --> 01:01.692
WHY DON´T WE PLAY TEAMS?

01:01.692 --> 01:03.364
THAT´S A GOOD IDEA.

01:03.364 --> 01:05.496
THAT´S A GREAT IDEA!

01:05.496 --> 01:07.338
EVERYONE, SIT DOWN!

01:07.338 --> 01:10.171
WE COULD PLAY ALL NIGHT!

01:10.171 --> 01:13.344
NEVER MESS WITH A GUY
WITH NO LIFE.

01:13.344 --> 01:16.177
SO, VIC,
HOW ARE THEY HANGING?

01:16.177 --> 01:19.610
I WAS JUST GOING TO ASK YOU
THE SAME THING, BENNY.

01:22.253 --> 01:24.355
NOW, IT´S YOUR HOUSE.

01:24.355 --> 01:26.457
YOU PLACE
THE FIRST BONE.

01:29.390 --> 01:32.363
[ MUTTERS IN SPANISH ]

01:32.363 --> 01:33.364
WHAT?

01:33.364 --> 01:35.826
YOU PLAY
LIKE A WOMAN.

01:35.826 --> 01:38.129
A REAL MAN PUTS
HIS BONE ON THE TABLE

01:38.129 --> 01:39.630
WITH AUTHORITY.

01:39.630 --> 01:43.774
THAT´S HOW IT´S DONE!
I APOLOGIZE FOR MY DAUGHTER!

01:45.536 --> 01:47.538
HEY, MAX, WHY DON´T
YOU SIT IN FOR ME?

01:47.538 --> 01:49.680
THAT´S OKAY. I PLAYED
ALL AFTERNOON.

01:49.680 --> 01:52.483
NO --
NO, NO, COME ON.
SIT IN.

01:54.515 --> 01:56.287
YOU´RE IN, BROTHER!

01:56.287 --> 01:57.688
CRAP!

01:57.688 --> 02:00.151
YOU´RE ABOUT TO PLAY
THE MOST EXCITING GAME

02:00.151 --> 02:01.622
TO COME OUT OF CUBA

02:01.622 --> 02:04.124
SINCE THEY INVENTED
"WHEEL OF MISFORTUNE"!

02:04.124 --> 02:05.796
I´D LIKE
TO BUY A VOWEL...

02:05.796 --> 02:09.830
THERE ARE NO VOWELS BECAUSE
CASTRO HAS DETAINED THEM ALL!

02:11.602 --> 02:13.604
HEY, HONEY, THIS IS
MY FRIEND NICOLE.

02:13.604 --> 02:15.566
SHE SELLS LA MARIE
COSMETICS, TOO.

02:15.566 --> 02:17.768
HEY, NICE TO MEET YOU.
HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

02:17.768 --> 02:20.341
WELL, YOU DIDN´T TELL ME
YOUR HUSBAND WAS SO HANDSOME.

02:20.341 --> 02:23.344
NICOLE, YOU ARE NOT GOING
TO SELL HIM ANYTHING.

02:23.344 --> 02:26.477
HOW DO YOU KNOW SHE´S
TRYING TO SELL ME SOMETHING?

02:26.477 --> 02:29.220
MAYBE SHE THINKS
I´M HANDSOME.

02:29.220 --> 02:31.922
YOU ARE. I MEAN,
THE HAIR AND THOSE EYES...

02:31.922 --> 02:34.385
YOU KNOW, IF YOU JUST USE
A LITTLE MOISTURIZER --

02:34.385 --> 02:36.887
SOLD!

02:36.887 --> 02:38.689
YOU ARE GOOD,

02:38.689 --> 02:41.392
BUT YOU´RE STILL NOT WINNING
THAT SALES TITLE NEXT MONTH.

02:41.392 --> 02:42.733
OH, YES, I AM.

02:42.733 --> 02:44.595
YOU ARE GOING DOWN,
GIRLFRIEND.

02:44.595 --> 02:47.238
OH, BRING IT ON.
OH, IT IS ON.

02:47.238 --> 02:49.300
HEY, IF YOU COULD DO THIS
IN A KIDDIE POOL

02:49.300 --> 02:52.203
FILLED WITH MUD,
YOU COULD MAKE SOME MONEY.

02:52.203 --> 02:54.245
THAT´S MY MOM.
SHE´S JUST CRANKY

02:54.245 --> 02:56.547
´CAUSE WE SWITCHED HER
TO DRY FOOD.

02:56.547 --> 02:59.410
ANGIE, IF YOU´RE COMING WITH ME,
WE SHOULD GET GOING.

02:59.410 --> 03:01.682
OH, YEAH, GEORGE, I´M GOING
TO AN ART GALLERY TONIGHT

03:01.682 --> 03:03.514
WITH NICOLE.
ALL RIGHT.

03:03.514 --> 03:05.756
YEAH, AND I WANT TO GET THERE
EARLY TO CHECK OUT THE GUYS

03:05.756 --> 03:07.418
BEFORE I START DRINKING.

03:07.418 --> 03:09.460
YOU´RE GOING TO HAVE SLOW
YOUR ROLL DOWN TONIGHT.

03:09.460 --> 03:11.762
I MEAN, YOU GOT AN OLD
MARRIED LADY WITH YOU.

03:11.762 --> 03:13.624
WELL, I DON´T THINK SO.

03:13.624 --> 03:15.426
SHE IS MY RAVEN-HAIRED
MAN MAGNET.

03:15.426 --> 03:18.229
MM-HMM, JUST SIGNAL ME
WHEN YOU WANT A HAIR FLIP.

03:18.229 --> 03:20.371
[ Coughs ] WHORES!

03:24.475 --> 03:26.737
I´M GOING TO MAKE A COUPLE
OF CALLS FROM THE CAR,

03:26.737 --> 03:28.839
BUT WE REALLY SHOULD
GET GOING.

03:28.839 --> 03:31.242
I HAVE TO CHANGE
INTO SOMETHING SEXIER.

03:31.242 --> 03:33.244
SEXIER? WHAT´S SHE GOING
TO WEAR --

03:33.244 --> 03:35.846
A CORN CHIP
AND TWO DIMES?

03:35.846 --> 03:38.218
UM, MOM, MY ROOM´S
TOO SMALL.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.351
CAN I HAVE THE SLEEPOVER
IN THE LIVING ROOM?

03:40.351 --> 03:42.553
IT´S UP TO YOUR FATHER.
HE´S IN CHARGE TONIGHT.

03:42.553 --> 03:45.396
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
I´M IN CHARGE OF A SLEEPOVER?

03:45.396 --> 03:47.458
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS. YOU SAID
YOU´D TAKE THE NEXT SLEEPOVER

03:47.458 --> 03:49.960
IF I WENT TO THE LAST
PARENT-TEACHER CONFERENCE.

03:49.960 --> 03:51.432
I WENT
TO THAT CONFERENCE.

03:51.432 --> 03:53.404
I REMEMBER THERE WAS,
UM, GOLD STARS

03:53.404 --> 03:56.737
AND, UH, THE MAYFLOWER
MADE OUT OF TOOTHPICKS.

03:56.737 --> 03:59.610
THAT WAS FOURTH GRADE.

03:59.610 --> 04:03.614
WHAT GRADE IS SHE IN NOW?

04:03.614 --> 04:05.916
ALL RIGHT,
I´LL HANDLE IT.

04:05.916 --> 04:08.018
I BETTER HURRY
AND GET READY.

04:08.018 --> 04:10.481
LOOK, DAD, THESE ARE GIRLS
FROM ALLENDALE.

04:10.481 --> 04:11.552
SO?

04:11.552 --> 04:12.923
SO TONIGHT,

04:12.923 --> 04:15.626
CAN YOU TRY TO BE
A LITTLE MORE SOPHISTICATED?

04:15.626 --> 04:18.489
[ Southern accent ] WELL,
YOU DON´T NEED TO FRET NOW,

04:18.489 --> 04:19.960
LITTLE FILLY.

04:19.960 --> 04:22.433
I AIN´T GONNA TRY
TO TAKE NONE

04:22.433 --> 04:24.565
OF YOUR BOOK-LEARNIN´,
HIGH-FALLUTIN´ FRIENDS

04:24.565 --> 04:26.497
AS A BRIDE.

04:26.497 --> 04:26.867
YEE-HOO!

04:40.781 --> 04:42.282
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS ♫

04:42.282 --> 04:46.286
♫ KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

05:14.445 --> 05:17.648
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYING ]

05:22.753 --> 05:25.325
THAT´S IT! I TOLD YOU
TO TURN THE MUSIC DOWN

05:25.325 --> 05:26.757
THREE TIMES!

05:26.757 --> 05:28.899
AND STOP DANCING!

05:28.899 --> 05:30.901
AND NO MORE TRUTH OR DARE

05:30.901 --> 05:33.764
UNTIL SOMEBODY
RETURNS MY UNDERWEAR.

05:36.367 --> 05:39.009
[ ALL GIGGLING ]

05:39.009 --> 05:41.011
Girl: HOW COULD THIS
HAPPEN TO ME?

05:41.011 --> 05:43.013
NOW NOTHING SEEMS RIGHT, AND I
DON´T SEE HOW IT´S POSSIBLE

05:43.013 --> 05:45.376
HE COULDN´T LIKE ME BUT HE´S
ALWAYS REALLY NICE TO ME.

05:45.376 --> 05:47.618
IT JUST DOESN´T
MAKE SENSE TO ME.

05:47.618 --> 05:49.480
WHAT´S WRONG?

05:49.480 --> 05:50.951
NOTHING.

05:50.951 --> 05:53.353
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES
IT´S EASIER TO TELL SOMEONE

05:53.353 --> 05:56.056
WHO´S NOT A FRIEND
OR A PARENT.

05:56.056 --> 05:59.029
OKAY. ALEX TOLD JENNY
THAT SASHA TOLD HER

05:59.029 --> 06:01.061
THAT ZACK DOESN´T LIKE ME.

06:01.061 --> 06:03.864
I LIKE KEVIN, BUT I ALSO
KIND OF LIKE ZACK, TOO.

06:03.864 --> 06:06.397
AND I DON´T SEE HOW
IT´S POSSIBLE --

06:12.873 --> 06:16.647
HOW CAN YOU PICK HIM
OVER ME?

06:16.647 --> 06:18.409
YOU BARELY KNOW HIM.

06:19.910 --> 06:23.484
I HOPE HE´S NOT TALKING TO
A LITTLE GIRL IN A SLEEPING BAG.

06:29.059 --> 06:32.463
I LEFT MIAMI TO GIVE YOU
TIME TO THINK.

06:32.463 --> 06:35.526
NO, THIS IS NOT WHAT
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO THINK.

06:35.526 --> 06:37.167
YOU´RE SORRY?

06:37.167 --> 06:39.129
NO, NO,
DON´T APOLOGIZE TO ME.

06:39.129 --> 06:41.772
APOLOGIZE TO GOD
FOR DESTROYING 40 YEARS

06:41.772 --> 06:44.835
OF MARRIAGE!

06:44.835 --> 06:47.838
WOW!

06:47.838 --> 06:51.842
THIS DOESN´T TASTE
LIKE ONE CALORIE!

06:51.842 --> 06:54.815
DON´T PRETEND
YOU DIDN´T HEAR.

06:54.815 --> 06:56.987
EMELINA´S DIVORCING ME.

06:56.987 --> 06:58.188
WHAT?

06:58.188 --> 07:00.491
I DON´T KNOW
HOW IT HAPPENED TO ME.

07:00.491 --> 07:02.753
I DON´T EVEN KNOW HOW
TO SAY THIS.

07:02.753 --> 07:05.926
I´VE BEEN CUCKOLDED!

07:07.598 --> 07:08.599
I´M SORRY?

07:08.599 --> 07:11.902
CUCKOLDED.

07:11.902 --> 07:14.635
I´M TRYING
TO BE SYMPATHETIC HERE.

07:14.635 --> 07:17.968
I JUST HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU´RE SAYING.

07:17.968 --> 07:20.140
MY WIFE CHEATED ON ME.

07:20.140 --> 07:23.744
LAST WEEK, I WENT TO HER
DERMATOLOGY CLINIC

07:23.744 --> 07:25.145
TO SURPRISE HER.

07:25.145 --> 07:27.978
I WALKED IN ON HER
CHECKING A MAN FOR MOLES

07:27.978 --> 07:31.451
IN A PLACE WHERE SUN DAMAGE
IS NOT A POSSIBILITY.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.487
OH, ANGIE´S GOING
TO BE DEVASTATED.

07:36.487 --> 07:39.790
GEORGE, YOU MUST ALLOW ME
TO TELL MY DAUGHTER

07:39.790 --> 07:42.633
IN MY OWN WAY,
IN MY OWN TIME.

07:42.633 --> 07:44.735
WELL, MAYBE YOU WON´T
HAVE TO TELL ANGIE.

07:44.735 --> 07:46.897
MAYBE EMELINA WILL REALIZE
THAT THIS IS A MISTAKE.

07:46.897 --> 07:48.899
VIC, YOU GUYS HAVE
A GREAT MARRIAGE.

07:48.899 --> 07:51.602
THAT´S WHAT I THOUGHT.

07:51.602 --> 07:53.604
BUT IT ALL CAME OUT.

07:53.604 --> 07:55.175
THIS WASN´T THE FIRST TIME.

07:55.175 --> 07:58.108
I SHOULD HAVE SEEN IT
COMING.

07:58.108 --> 08:01.081
SHE WAS WORKING MORE,
COMING HOME LATE.

08:01.081 --> 08:06.186
SHE STARTED GOING OUT
WITH HER GIRLFRIENDS AGAIN.

08:06.186 --> 08:08.659
WELL, HEY, LOTS OF HAPPILY
MARRIED WOMEN GO OUT

08:08.659 --> 08:11.191
WITH THEIR GIRLFRIENDS. THAT
DOESN´T MEAN ANYTHING, RIGHT?

08:11.191 --> 08:13.824
I NEVER THOUGHT
THIS COULD HAPPEN TO ME.

08:13.824 --> 08:16.496
I MEAN, I-I STAYED FIT.

08:16.496 --> 08:20.571
I WAS SUCCESSFUL.
I KEPT THE ROMANCE ALIVE.

08:20.571 --> 08:22.603
FOR WHAT?

08:22.603 --> 08:24.905
I LOOK AT YOU AND THINK
MAYBE YOU´RE RIGHT.

08:24.905 --> 08:27.938
WHY EVEN TRY?

08:33.814 --> 08:36.687
[ GIRLS WHISPERING,
GIGGLING ]

08:36.687 --> 08:38.218
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:38.218 --> 08:41.922
AAH!
AAH!

08:43.954 --> 08:46.627
GO TO BED!

08:55.836 --> 08:59.309
[ Gasps ] JEEZ!

08:59.309 --> 09:01.872
HEY, LOOK WHAT
THE CAT DRAGGED IN.

09:01.872 --> 09:03.974
YOU WAITED UP.

09:05.646 --> 09:07.618
WHAT´S WITH THE CLOCK?

09:07.618 --> 09:09.620
I THINK IT´S FAST.

09:09.620 --> 09:11.952
I´M CHECKING MY WATCH.
DOES YOUR WATCH SHOW

09:11.952 --> 09:14.254
THAT IT´S 10 PAST FIVE HOURS
AFTER YOU SHOULD´VE BEEN HOME?

09:14.254 --> 09:16.286
OH, HONEY, I´M SORRY.

09:16.286 --> 09:19.159
I WAS JUST HAVING
SO MUCH FUN WITH NICOLE.

09:19.159 --> 09:23.894
YOU SHOULD´VE CALLED.

09:23.894 --> 09:25.796
YOU´RE MAD.

09:25.796 --> 09:28.599
THERE´S LIPSTICK
ON YOUR SHIRT!

09:28.599 --> 09:32.002
I KNOW. IT´S MINE.

09:32.002 --> 09:36.046
YOU´RE JUST FULL OF ANSWERS
TONIGHT, AREN´T YOU?

09:38.178 --> 09:41.351
YEAH. AND IF YOU SMELL ME,

09:41.351 --> 09:43.313
I SMELL LIKE PERFUME.

09:43.313 --> 09:45.015
AND IF YOU SEARCH ME,

09:45.015 --> 09:48.889
YOU´RE GOING TO FIND A PAIR
OF WOMEN´S PANTIES.

09:48.889 --> 09:51.321
WHERE IS ALL THIS
COMING FROM?

09:51.321 --> 09:55.125
TELL ME.

09:55.125 --> 09:59.229
WHAT DO YOU THINK
I WAS DOING TONIGHT?

10:01.001 --> 10:03.303
DO YOU THINK
I WAS CHEATING ON YOU?

10:03.303 --> 10:07.277
GUILT!

10:07.277 --> 10:09.640
ARE YOU CRAZY?

10:09.640 --> 10:11.712
WE HAVE BEEN MARRIED
FOR 16 YEARS.

10:11.712 --> 10:13.784
WE HAVE TWO KIDS
AND A HOUSE TOGETHER.

10:13.784 --> 10:15.716
AH, SO...

10:15.716 --> 10:19.249
SO YOU´RE FEELING TRAPPED.

10:19.249 --> 10:22.052
NO!

10:22.052 --> 10:24.094
ARE YOU
FEELING TRAPPED?

10:24.094 --> 10:26.096
HEY, DON´T TURN THIS
ON ME, ANGIE.

10:26.096 --> 10:29.029
I´M THE ONE
WHO´S FAITHFUL.

10:29.029 --> 10:31.361
WHY ARE YOU BEING
SUCH A JERK?

10:31.361 --> 10:33.333
NO, I´LL TELL YOU WHY.

10:33.333 --> 10:35.165
TELL ME WHY.

10:35.165 --> 10:37.938
BECAUSE YOU COME FROM
A DYSFUNCTIONAL FAMILY!

10:37.938 --> 10:40.640
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT A GOOD MARRIAGE IS.

10:40.640 --> 10:43.143
YOU KNOW, MAYBE -- MAYBE
IF YOU PAID MORE ATTENTION

10:43.143 --> 10:44.945
TO MY PARENTS,

10:44.945 --> 10:47.147
YOU MIGHT LEARN A LITTLE
SOMETHING ABOUT LOVE AND TRUST!

10:47.147 --> 10:48.819
GOOD NIGHT!

10:48.819 --> 10:51.882
WHY ARE YOU GOING UPSTAIRS?
THE SOFA´S THAT WAY!

10:51.882 --> 10:53.283
THAT´S WHERE --

10:58.288 --> 11:00.030
FINE!

11:00.030 --> 11:02.192
I´LL HAVE MY OWN SLUMBER
PARTY OUTSIDE!

11:02.192 --> 11:05.065
I´LL PUT TWO LAWN CHAIRS
TOGETHER. I DON´T CARE.

11:05.065 --> 11:07.367
I GREW UP OUTSIDE.
I´M NOT SCARED.

11:07.367 --> 11:09.700
I WAS RAISED BY WOLVES,

11:09.700 --> 11:12.342
AND I USED TO EAT BERRIES
AT NIGHT.

11:15.806 --> 11:17.848
[ MUTTERS IN SPANISH ]

11:24.284 --> 11:27.117
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

11:30.921 --> 11:32.322
VIC?

11:32.322 --> 11:34.224
iAY!

11:34.224 --> 11:36.366
GEORGE, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

11:36.366 --> 11:38.368
LOOK, I HAD A FIGHT
WITH ANGIE

11:38.368 --> 11:40.370
AND MADE A FOOL
OUT OF MYSELF, MAN.

11:40.370 --> 11:42.432
YOU GOTTA TELL HER
ABOUT YOU AND EMELINA.

11:42.432 --> 11:44.704
WHAT DOES ONE HAVE TO DO
WITH THE OTHER?

11:44.704 --> 11:46.737
YOU GOT IN MY HEAD, MAN,
WITH ALL THAT CRAZY TALK

11:46.737 --> 11:48.909
ABOUT HOW IT COULD HAPPEN
TO ANYONE.

11:48.909 --> 11:51.842
CUCKOLDED!
I WAS CUCKOLDED!

11:51.842 --> 11:54.714
LOOK, ANGIE WILL UNDERSTAND
WHY I GOT SO JEALOUS

11:54.714 --> 11:56.286
IF YOU TELL HER
ABOUT THE DIVORCE.

11:56.286 --> 11:58.789
NO. SHE IDOLIZES
HER MOTHER.

11:58.789 --> 12:01.321
LISTEN, ANGIE AND I DON´T
FIGHT THAT OFTEN

12:01.321 --> 12:03.353
AND WHEN WE DO, WE USUALLY
CLEAR THINGS UP PRETTY QUICKLY.

12:03.353 --> 12:06.156
LOOK, I DON´T WANT TO BE
LIKE THIS WITH HER, VIC,

12:06.156 --> 12:07.858
SO YOU GOTTA HELP ME.

12:07.858 --> 12:10.230
I CAN´T. MY LITTLE GIRL
WILL THINK I´M A FAILURE.

12:10.230 --> 12:13.163
SURE, YOU MAY BE USED TO IT,
BUT I HAVE MY PRIDE.

12:13.163 --> 12:14.905
TRUST ME,
WHEN YOU TELL ANGIE,

12:14.905 --> 12:16.867
SHE´S NOT GOING
TO THINK ANY LESS OF YOU.

12:16.867 --> 12:19.169
YOU´RE HER FATHER, AND YOU´RE
NOT A FAILURE AT THAT.

12:19.169 --> 12:21.741
OKAY, GEORGE.

12:21.741 --> 12:24.845
I DON´T WANT
TO RUIN YOUR MARRIAGE, TOO.

12:24.845 --> 12:27.517
OR NOT ANYMORE, I DON´T.

12:27.517 --> 12:29.449
I´LL TELL HER.

12:29.449 --> 12:31.451
AND, YOU KNOW,
I COULDN´T SAY THIS

12:31.451 --> 12:33.924
WHILE YOU GUYS WERE TOGETHER,
BUT EMELINA -- OH, MAN...

12:33.924 --> 12:37.757
SHE WAS ONE BITTER TRAMP WITH
A 10-FOOT STICK UP HER BUTT.

12:37.757 --> 12:41.031
SHE´S THE MOTHER
OF MY CHILDREN,

12:41.031 --> 12:42.762
A GIFTED DOCTOR,

12:42.762 --> 12:45.265
AND THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
WOMAN IN THE WORLD.

12:45.265 --> 12:47.437
OKAY, TOO SOON.

12:51.541 --> 12:53.143
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

12:53.143 --> 12:55.445
OH, NO, YOU KNOW WHAT YOU´RE
GOING TO HAVE TO DO

12:55.445 --> 12:57.848
TO GET BACK IN THIS ROOM.

12:57.848 --> 13:00.180
Vic: WHAT IS THAT?

13:00.180 --> 13:02.452
OH, DADDY, I THOUGHT
IT WAS GEORGE.

13:02.452 --> 13:04.855
WELL, WHAT DOES
HE HAVE TO DO?

13:04.855 --> 13:06.386
LET IT GO.

13:06.386 --> 13:09.489
WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP
SO LATE?

13:09.489 --> 13:13.123
SOMETHING´S WRONG.
COME IN.

13:13.123 --> 13:16.226
YES.

13:16.226 --> 13:17.427
WELL, I...

13:17.427 --> 13:20.230
HAVE SOMETHING
TO TELL YOU.

13:20.230 --> 13:22.873
IT´S NOT EASY.

13:22.873 --> 13:24.434
WELL, JUST TELL ME.

13:24.434 --> 13:26.006
OKAY.

13:26.006 --> 13:29.910
YOU KNOW HOW CUBA
AND THE UNITED STATES

13:29.910 --> 13:33.383
USED TO HAVE RELATIONS
AND THEN THEY GREW APART?

13:33.383 --> 13:35.986
DADDY, IS THIS LIKE
WHEN YOU SAID MY WEDDING NIGHT

13:35.986 --> 13:38.989
WOULD BE LIKE
THE BAY OF PIGS INVASION --

13:38.989 --> 13:40.991
QUICK AND A FAILURE?

13:40.991 --> 13:43.523
NO, ANGIE.

13:47.457 --> 13:52.933
IT´S YOUR MOTHER AND ME.

13:52.933 --> 13:54.935
WE ARE...

13:54.935 --> 13:57.868
HAVING PROBLEMS.

13:57.868 --> 13:59.940
WE´RE GETTING A DIVORCE.

13:59.940 --> 14:03.413
YOU´RE JOKING.

14:03.413 --> 14:07.047
YOU HAVE TO BE JOKING.

14:07.047 --> 14:09.249
I´M AFRAID NOT, MIJITA.

14:09.249 --> 14:10.850
I DON´T UNDERSTAND.

14:10.850 --> 14:12.622
BUT YOUR MOTHER...

14:12.622 --> 14:14.054
WHAT?

14:14.054 --> 14:18.188
WHAT ABOUT MOMMY?

14:18.188 --> 14:21.561
YOUR MOTHER...

14:21.561 --> 14:25.295
AND I JUST DRIFTED APART.

14:25.295 --> 14:28.298
THERE HAS TO BE
MORE THAN THAT.

14:28.298 --> 14:29.639
THERE ISN´T.

14:29.639 --> 14:33.273
THERE´S JUST NO SPARK
ANYMORE.

14:33.273 --> 14:39.209
BUT WE BOTH LOVE YOU
VERY MUCH.

14:39.209 --> 14:42.612
YOU WERE TOGETHER
FOR 40 YEARS.

14:44.955 --> 14:48.018
I THOUGHT YOU WOULD ALWAYS
BE TOGETHER.

14:48.018 --> 14:51.891
ME TOO.

15:03.433 --> 15:06.606
I NEED SOME COMFORT FOOD.

15:06.606 --> 15:08.538
GOOD LUCK. THOSE GIRLS
CLEANED US OUT.

15:08.538 --> 15:13.683
THE ONLY THING LEFT
ARE TACO SHELLS AND JELLY.

15:13.683 --> 15:17.187
SORRY ABOUT YOUR FOLKS,
ANGIE.

15:17.187 --> 15:19.689
YOU KNOW?

15:19.689 --> 15:21.621
I WAS THERE
WHEN YOUR MOM CALLED.

15:21.621 --> 15:24.094
THAT´S WHY
I GOT SO CRAZY.

15:24.094 --> 15:26.396
I STARTED TO THINK THAT
IF IT COULD HAPPEN TO THEM,

15:26.396 --> 15:28.928
IT COULD HAPPEN TO US.

15:28.928 --> 15:31.931
GEORGE, WE ARE NOT GOING
TO DRIFT APART.

15:36.336 --> 15:39.269
IS THAT WHAT YOUR DAD SAID,
"DRIFTED APART"?

15:39.269 --> 15:41.671
I JUST DON´T KNOW
HOW THIS HAPPENED.

15:41.671 --> 15:44.314
MAYBE THEY WERE
WORKING TOO MUCH.

15:44.314 --> 15:48.078
MAYBE SHE SPENT TOO MUCH TIME
AT THE DERMATOLOGY CLINIC.

15:52.222 --> 15:54.684
GETTING WARMER...

15:54.684 --> 15:56.987
I´M GOING
TO CALL MY MOM.

15:56.987 --> 16:00.290
YOU CAN´T FIX THIS, ANGIE.
IT´S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

16:00.290 --> 16:02.632
WHAT´S NOT SIMPLE
ABOUT IT?

16:04.294 --> 16:08.368
YOUR MOM HAD AN AFFAIR.

16:12.142 --> 16:14.444
I´M SORRY.

16:18.008 --> 16:20.010
OKAY. IT HAPPENS.

16:20.010 --> 16:22.312
BUT MARRIAGES
GET OVER THESE THINGS.

16:22.312 --> 16:26.016
IT WAS JUST
ONE MISTAKE, RIGHT?

16:29.389 --> 16:32.122
[ GIRLS LAUGHING ]

16:34.024 --> 16:36.066
[ GIRL SHUSHES ]

16:41.031 --> 16:43.133
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:43.133 --> 16:44.334
NOTHING.

16:44.334 --> 16:46.176
IT´S 3:00
IN THE MORNING.

16:46.176 --> 16:48.738
WHY THE HELL ARE YOU BUILDING
A PYRAMID IN MY LIVING ROOM?

16:48.738 --> 16:51.581
HOW MANY TIMES DO I HAVE
TO TELL YOU?

16:51.581 --> 16:53.783
NO PYRAMIDS
IN THE LIVING ROOM!

16:53.783 --> 16:56.686
IT´S A TRUST-BUILDING
EXERCISE.

16:56.686 --> 16:58.618
TRUST?

16:58.618 --> 17:01.551
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT TRUST?

17:01.551 --> 17:04.154
THIS PYRAMID...

17:04.154 --> 17:06.756
IT´S GONNA FALL.

17:06.756 --> 17:08.698
IT´S GONNA COME
CRUMBLING DOWN

17:08.698 --> 17:10.760
BECAUSE EVERYTHING DOES.

17:10.760 --> 17:15.265
AND YOU ARE ALL GOING
TO GET HURT.

17:15.265 --> 17:17.267
OKAY, TIME FOR BED.

17:17.267 --> 17:18.438
EVERYTHING´S OKAY.

17:18.438 --> 17:20.540
MRS. LOPEZ IS JUST
A LITTLE UPSET.

17:20.540 --> 17:22.372
IT´S A GREAT PYRAMID.
REALLY, IT IS.

17:22.372 --> 17:24.544
AND YOU DIDN´T WITHOUT
ANY FAT GIRLS ON THE BOTTOM.

17:24.544 --> 17:26.076
I´M VERY IMPRESSED.

17:30.480 --> 17:33.653
George: NICE HAVING YOU.
MOVE ALONG.

17:33.653 --> 17:37.627
YOU DON´T HAVE TO GO HOME,
BUT YOU CAN´T STAY HERE.

17:39.659 --> 17:42.132
HOW YOU DOING, BABY?

17:42.132 --> 17:43.663
I´M OKAY.

17:46.136 --> 17:47.797
HEY, DADDY, YOU WANT ME
TO FIX YOU SOME LUNCH?

17:47.797 --> 17:49.799
NO, NO, I JUST WENT
FOR A RUN.

17:49.799 --> 17:51.841
I HAVE A FLIGHT
TO CATCH.

17:51.841 --> 17:54.404
I HAVE THINGS TO TAKE CARE OF
WITH YOUR MOTHER.

17:54.404 --> 17:55.805
WHERE ARE YOU GOING TO STAY?

17:55.805 --> 17:58.308
YOU DON´T WANT TO GO BACK
TO THE HOUSE.

17:58.308 --> 18:00.150
DON´T WORRY.
I´LL BE FINE.

18:00.150 --> 18:02.852
I´M GOING TO
A GENTLEMEN´S HOTEL TO DIE.

18:07.317 --> 18:09.859
HEY, VIC.

18:09.859 --> 18:12.492
WHY DON´T YOU STAY HERE
A LITTLE WHILE LONGER?

18:12.492 --> 18:15.465
THAT´S A GREAT IDEA.

18:15.465 --> 18:17.467
I LOVE HAVING YOU AROUND,

18:17.467 --> 18:20.200
THE KIDS LOVE
HAVING YOU AROUND.

18:20.200 --> 18:23.203
YEAH, THEY DO.

18:23.203 --> 18:27.237
ALL RIGHT, I SUPPOSE I COULD
HANDLE THINGS BY PHONE.

18:27.237 --> 18:28.538
OKAY, I´LL STAY.

18:28.538 --> 18:31.311
BUT JUST
FOR A FEW WEEKS, HUH?

18:31.311 --> 18:33.843
[ MUTTERS IN SPANISH ]

18:33.843 --> 18:38.288
HEY, MAYBE I´LL EVEN
TEACH YOU ANOTHER CUBAN GAME!

18:38.288 --> 18:41.821
YEAH, I CAN´T WAIT TO PLAY
"EAT THE TAIL ON THE DONKEY."

18:45.255 --> 18:47.897
HOW ARE YOU REALLY FEELING?

18:47.897 --> 18:51.561
I FEEL LIKE SOMEBODY
PUNCHED ME IN THE STOMACH.

18:51.561 --> 18:53.303
I KNOW THAT FEELING.

18:53.303 --> 18:58.268
MY MOM USED TO PUNCH ME
IN THE STOMACH ALL THE TIME.

18:58.268 --> 19:01.671
I´M HOME -- BAM!

19:01.671 --> 19:05.675
HOW COULD MY MOM CHEAT
ON MY DAD?

19:05.675 --> 19:08.278
LOOK, BABY, I KNOW THIS
IS HARD FOR YOU.

19:08.278 --> 19:10.880
BUT IF YOU HAD GROWN UP
IN A DYSFUNCTIONAL FAMILY,

19:10.880 --> 19:15.425
YOU´D KNOW HOW TO DEAL
WITH THIS.

19:15.425 --> 19:18.358
YOU JUST DON´T HAVE THE TOOLS,
YOU KNOW,

19:18.358 --> 19:20.390
THAT I DO.

19:22.262 --> 19:24.464
SO, HOW WOULD YOU DEAL
WITH THIS?

19:24.464 --> 19:26.196
THIS? EASY.

19:26.196 --> 19:28.868
HAVE A SHOT OF TEQUILA
AND PRETEND IT NEVER HAPPENED.

19:30.340 --> 19:32.942
THAT´S NOT GOING
TO WORK FOR ME.

19:32.942 --> 19:37.807
THAT´S BECAUSE YOU´VE BEEN
CURSED BY LOVE AND HAPPINESS.

19:37.807 --> 19:40.480
IT´S CRIPPLED YOU.

19:40.480 --> 19:42.552
NOW, DON´T TALK ABOUT IT,

19:42.552 --> 19:46.286
REPRESS IT, AND DENY IT.

19:54.424 --> 19:58.298
BUT HOW DID MY MOTHER --

19:58.298 --> 20:00.230
ANGIE, I CAN´T HELP YOU

20:00.230 --> 20:04.404
IF YOU DON´T WANT
TO HELP YOURSELF.

20:10.410 --> 20:11.911
I FEEL BETTER.

20:18.718 --> 20:22.452
OKAY, ERNESTO, THIS IS HOW
A REAL MAN TRAINS.

20:22.452 --> 20:25.995
[ YELLING IN SPANISH ]

20:29.729 --> 20:31.831
COME ON, LITTLE BUDDIES.

20:31.831 --> 20:33.863
TWO MORE, AND YOU GET
A CHOCOLATE BAR.

20:33.863 --> 20:36.466
COME ON.

20:37.937 --> 20:40.440
OH, MAN.
IF YOU GUYS COULD DO THAT

20:40.440 --> 20:52.622
IN A KIDDIE POOL FULL OF MUD,
YOU´D MAKE SOME SERIOUS CASH.
